The paper deals with graph cut problems and clustering, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The focus on local objectives rather than global objectives suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The use of graph theory and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CG (computational geometry) or cs.LG (machine learning). Finally, the study of min-max graph cut problems and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.GT (computational game theory).
